<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="298" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,229,904]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,356,770,796]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Etymology:—</emphasis>
Named for the diatomist Dr. David Mann, for all of his efforts to uncover and resolve the riddles contained within the 
<taxonomicName box="[372,516,806,832]" class="Bacillariophyceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Bacillariales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="order">Bacillariales</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="298" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,229,904]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,356,841,868]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Comments:—</emphasis>
This delicate species was well-preserved in the ca. 9 million year-old sediments of the Esmeralda Formation.
</paragraph>
